+Name:           nodejs-chalk
+Version:        5.3.0
+Release:        0
+Summary:        Terminal string styling done right
+License:        MIT
+Group:          Development/Libraries/Other
+URL:            https://github.com/chalk/chalk
+Source0:        https://registry.npmjs.org/chalk/-/chalk-%{version}.tgz
+
+BuildRequires:  nodejs-devel
+BuildRequires:  nodejs-packaging
+BuildArch:      noarch
+
+%description
+Chalk is a terminal string styling library for Node.js. It allows you to
+easily add colors, backgrounds, and other text decorations to output in the
+terminal or console. It supports 256 colors and truecolor (16 million colors).
+
+%prep
+%setup -q -n package
+find . -name '*.node' -delete
+find . -name '*.jar' -delete
+find . -name '*.dll' -delete
+find . -name '*.exe' -delete
+find . -name '*.so' -delete
+find . -name '*.dylib' -delete
+
+%install
+mkdir -p %{buildroot}%{nodejs_sitelib}/%{name}
+cp -r source %{buildroot}%{nodejs_sitelib}/%{name}/
+cp package.json %{buildroot}%{nodejs_sitelib}/%{name}/
+%fdupes %{buildroot}
+
+%files
+%license license
+%doc readme.md
+%{nodejs_sitelib}/%{name}/
+
+%changelog
